6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to student mental health; mandating
the State Department of Education to create a school-
8 based telehealth pilot program; requiring the
Department to contract with a telehealth provider;
9 requiring a request for proposal; providing
definitions; specifying proposal requirements;
10 prescribing contract requirements; stating school
district participation requirements and limitations;
11 providing fund limitations; requiring the Department
and participating school districts to evaluate the
12 program; requiring reporting to the Legislature;
mandating school districts to report compliance with
13 certain provisions; requiring the Department to seek
funding; limiting expenditures; providing for
14 codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. The State Department of Education ("Department") shall
22 establish a school-based telehealth pilot program. The Department
23 shall contract with a single telehealth provider to provide mental
24 health care to students enrolled in participating school districts.
